Patient: How much water should I be drinking?

Healthcare Educator: Try to limit your fluid intake to less than 2 liters per day.

Patient: What happens if I have more than that?

Healthcare Educator: Too much fluid can make your heart work harder and cause shortness of breath.

Patient: What about the food I eat?

Healthcare Educator: Avoid high-sodium foods, they can cause your body to hold onto more fluid.

Patient: What should I do if I don't feel well?

Healthcare Educator: If you notice sudden weight gain or feel short of breath, reach out for medical help immediately.